sentences: Kes teab, kas me plaanist nahka saabki.
Ega nooremast pojastki paremat nahka tule kui vanemast.
Peeti ikka imelapseks, aga suurt nahka tast siiski ei tulnud.
context: Head is the partitive singular and nominative plural form of the Estonian adjective 'hea'. It means 'good' when referring to something in partitive case, or can be used in plural form meaning 'goods' or 'things'. The dictionary examples show it being used with the phrase 'nahka saama' (to get skin/guts) where 'head nahka' refers to having what it takes or meeting requirements.
